rComments: Despite only being a PHD student she is really caring and a great lecturer. She is accessible outside of class and wants to see all her students succeed. She has a real passion for teaching and wants to become a professor in the future. Hopefully she becomes future professor because great profs like her are rare to come by.

Ive been at Telfer for 4.5 years & Professor Tetzlaff is the best prof Ive had in this faculty. What stands out: her support towards students, her humour, & the guest speakers she brings in. Its a fun course because its not too difficult but u still learn a LOT of interesting + applicable content - best of both worlds. Highly recommend!
